The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Slim rise in Castrol profit

 OUR BUREAU

 July 19: Castrol India Ltd today reported a 4.98 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 49.49 crore for the quarter ended June 30 compared with Rs 47.14 crore in the year-ago period.

 Total income has increased 9.28 per cent to Rs 398.42 crore from Rs 364.58 crore, Castrol informed the Bombay Stock Exchange.

 The board has decided to pay an interim dividend of Rs 4 per share for the year ending December 31.

 Geometric Q1 net up

 Geometric Software Solutions Co Ltd today reported a 46.53 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 5.07 crore for the first quarter of this fiscal compared with Rs 3.46 crore in the same period last year. 

 Total income surged 40.49 per cent to Rs 31.64 crore from Rs 22.52 crore last year, the company informed the BSE.

 The group has posted a consolidated net profit of Rs 7.79 crore against Rs 5.10 crore in the year-ago quarter. 

 Clearly, the quarterly results are not satisfactory. We remain confident of our strategy and direction and the quarter represents a temporary setback, said Manu Parpia, managing director.

 Hexaware Tech

 Hexaware Technologies Ltd today reported a 104 per cent rise in net profit at Rs 15.14 crore for the quarter ended June 30 against Rs 7.42 crore in the corresponding previous quarter.

 Total income has increased 40 per cent to Rs 85.53 crore from Rs 61.05 crore last year, the company informed the BSE.

 The group has posted a consolidated profit after tax of Rs 19.45 crore against Rs 14.20 crore for the same quarter in 2004-05.

 Total income has increased to Rs 167.01 crore from Rs 132.74 crore last fiscal.




